results.name: Irregular triangle read by rows in which row n lists the numbers k such that the largest Dyck path of the symmetric representation of sigma(k) contains the point (n,n), or row n is 0 if no such k exists.
comment: For more information about the mentioned Dyck paths see A237593.
xref: Positive terms give A000027, the natural numbers.
Cf. A259179(n) is the number of positive terms in row n.
